ce:section.ce:para:
To investigate whether the increased red emission induced by DPA is specific, the fluorescence spectra of hPEI-CD-EDTA-Eu3+ nanoprobe solution upon addition of possible interferents were measured. During the selectivity study, metal ions, anions, and amino acids, including K+, Na+, Ca2+ Mg2+ NO3
                        −, Cl−, BA, Cys, Ala, Glu, and Asp were considered under the same conditions. As manifested in Fig. 4B, only DPA caused dramatic increment of I616/I440 ratio, none of interferents could induce a conspicuous fluorescence variation as DPA did at the same concentration. Moreover, the tolerances of the proposed hPEI-CD-EDTA-Eu3+ nanoprobe toward these possible interferents were also investigated. It is satisfactory that the detection of DPA using the designed hPEI-CD-EDTA-Eu3+ nanoprobe functioned well even with the existence of over 100-folds different interferents (Table S2), revealing the possibility for the practical DPA sensing in complicated environments. Taken together, hPEI-CD-EDTA-Eu3+ nanoprobe affords an effective and ratiometric platform for the DPA analysis (Table 1
                        ) [6–9,28,30–35].
